  ## AI Integration Patterns
  Gemini API Best Practices

  Rate Limiting & Retries

  - Implement exponential backoff for API calls
  - Track requests per minute (RPM) and tokens per minute (TPM)
  - Use circuit breaker pattern for API failures
  - Cache results to minimize API calls

  Prompt Engineering

  - Use structured prompts with clear field definitions
  - Implement few-shot learning with document examples
  - Add input/output format specifications
  - Include confidence scoring in extraction requests

  Error Handling

  - Handle RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED with backoff
  - Catch SAFETY_SETTINGS violations gracefully
  - Retry on INTERNAL_ERROR (500) responses
  - Log all API errors with request context

  Cost Optimization

  - Use Gemini Flash for simple extractions
  - Use Gemini Pro for complex analysis requiring reasoning
  - Implement smart caching based on document hash
  - Track token usage per job for billing

  ## Document Processing Workflow
  AI-Powered Extraction Pipeline

  Processing Steps

  1. Document upload and validation
  2. Convert PDF to text/images using pypdf + PIL
  3. Generate structured extraction prompt
  4. Call Gemini API with document content
  5. Parse and validate AI response
  6. Store results with confidence scores

